Translation from German......"He was a founding member of Kyuss and also played drums with Fu Manchu. For his buddy Josh Homme, he acted as a catalyst in the founding of the Queens Of The Stone Age. Brant Bjork, on the road since 1999, is one of the pioneers of the Stoner Rock. For many, he is the godfather of the genre.At some point he stopped counting her. And that's why Brant Bjork really does not know exactly how many albums he has published or how many he has been instrumental in. However, it is clear that as a musician, producer and head of his own record label, Brant Bjork, born in 1973, has long since become a hero status for his fans. And is either apostrophized as "icon" or "legend".Brant Bjork was a founding member of Kyuss, was also in Fu Manchu on drum kit and is still a multi-instrumentalist. His solo debut "Jalamanta" he played in 1999 with guitar, bass and drums completely himself. As a drummer of Kyuss and Fu Manchu, he became the forerunner of Stoner Rock when the genre was labeled as "Desert Rock". For many fans of the style direction he is considered a "godfather" of the style direction. With this praise, the musician who knows his buddy Josh Homme since high school times, little start. "I do not want to be the godfather of whatever-whatsoever," Brant Bjork said in an interview. "I'd rather see myself as a shaman. In the sense that I travel and with my music inspire other people to make music themselves. "Whether shaman, icon or Godfather: Brant Bjork's solo album from 2018 is called "Mankind Woman" and is brimming with energy. And it is, as the artist says, like all his albums and for example, a song like "Too Many Chiefs ... (Not Enough Indians"), "political".Category"
